  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study investigates the benefit of using chlorhexidine gel as an antimicrobial agent in
      orthodontic patient to reduce caries risk and the possible consequential effect of this use
      on the orthodontic brackets used for the treatment.

      The investigators hypothesis is that chlorhexidine gel use can reduce caries risk in
      orthodontic patients with out causing damage to the bonded ceramic or metal orthodontic
      brackets.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
